EA20200820 Report

Robin B. Trayler

August, 21, 2020

The \(\delta^{13}C\) and \(\delta^{15}N\) values and elemental carbon and nitrogen contents of all samples were measured using a Costech 4010 Elemental Analyzer coupled with a Delta V Plus Continuous Flow Isotope Ratio Mass Spectrometer housed in the Stable Isotope Facility at the University of California, Merced.

This report includes several files:

  1. A .html or .pdf report summarizing all data corrections and instrument reproducibility
  2. A .csv file with the corrected data
  3. A .csv file with the uncorrected data
  4. A .Rmd (R Markdown) document containing the R code used to correct the data

If you would like the original Isodat 3.0 .dxf files please request by sending an email to stableisotopes@ucmerced.edu

Setup

File Path

# file path to the isodat csv file 
file_path <- '~/Box Sync/Data Repository/EA/EA20200820.csv'

Analysis Parameters

Select Sample Peaks

# Which peak is the N2 analyte?
nitrogen_peak <- 3
# Which peak is the CO2 analyte?
carbon_peak <- 4
# How many total peaks should there be?
total_peaks <- 2

Set Rejection Criteria

# rejection criteria
small_peaks <- 500 # warn about peaks smaller with an amplitude smaller than this
# should 2 sigma outlier standards be dropped from isotope corrections
drop_outliers <- TRUE

Select Correction Standards

# standards used in run
standards_used = c('USGS 41a', 'USGS 40')
# material to use for linearity corrections
linearity_material = c('costech acetanilide')
# material to use for drift corrections
drift_material = c('costech acetanilide')
# material to use for weight calculations
weight_percent_material = c('USGS 40', 'USGS 41a', 'costech acetanilide')
# in house 'check' materials for run quality
check_material = c('EA sed', 'MB squid', 'peach')

Drift and Linearity Model Specification

Instrument Drift

# should a drift correction be applied to nitrogen
nitrogen_drift <- TRUE
# model choices are either 'lm' for linear or 'loess' for loess
nitrogen_drift_model <- 'lm'

# should a drift correction be applied to carbon
carbon_drift <- TRUE
# model choices are either 'lm' for linear or 'loess' for loess
carbon_drift_model <- 'lm'

Mass Linearity

# should a linearity correction be applied?
# mass linearity corrections use a linear model
nitrogen_linearity <- TRUE
carbon_linearity <- TRUE

Data Screening

## Warning in .parse_hms(..., order = "HMS", quiet = quiet): Some strings failed to parse, or all strings are NAs

Check for Missing Peaks

Sample(s) with an Identifier 1 of NA have fewer peaks than expected. Please check the raw data.

Check for Small Peaks

Sample(s) with an Identifier 1 of 6248 have a mass 28 (nitrogen) amplitude smaller than 500 mV. Data from these samples may be unreliable.

Sample(s) with an Identifier 1 of 6262, 6289, 6293 have a mass 44 (carbon) amplitude smaller than 500 mV. Data from these samples may be unreliable.

Drift Correction

Nitrogen Drift Correction

Nitrogen isotope compositional drift over the period of analysis was monitored using the costech acetanilide reference material(s). Since a drift correction was requested, A linear model was subtracted from the raw data.

Carbon Drift Correction

Carbon isotope compositional drift over the period of analysis was monitored using the costech acetanilide reference material(s). Since a drift correction was requested, A linear model was subtracted from the raw data.

Linearity Corrections

Nitrogen Linearity Correction

Mass linearity of nitrogen isotope compositions was monitored using the costech acetanilide reference material(s). Since a linearity correction was requested, A linear trend with an \(r^2\) of 0.01 was subtracted from the raw data.

Carbon Linearity Correction

Mass linearity of carbon isotope compositions was monitored using the costech acetanilide reference material(s). Since a linearity correction was requested, A linear trend with an \(r^2\) of 0 was subtracted from the raw data.

Standardization

The isotope composition of unknowns samples were corrected to the international PDB (\(\delta^{13}C\)) and Air (\(\delta^{15}N\)) scales using the USGS 41a and USGS 40 standard reference materials. Isotope compositions for standard reference materials are shown in the Table 1.

Table 1: Certified isotope compositions for standard reference materials
standard \(\delta^{13}C\) \(\delta^{15}N\)
USGS 40 -26.39 -4.52
USGS 41a 36.55 47.55

Elemental Content

Total carbon and nitrogen contents were calculated using the USGS 40 and USGS 41a and costech acetanilide reference materials. Certified carbon and nitrogen contents for these reference materials are shown in the Table 2.

Table 2: Certified elemental contents for standard reference materials
standard \(C \%\) \(N \%\)
USGS 40 40.80 9.52
USGS 41a 40.80 9.52
costech acetanilide 71.09 10.36
